WEBVTT

00:42.667 --> 00:45.211
SOLD OUT ON YOU

00:51.009 --> 00:55.597
Want perfection? Me too. So keep
out of my way.

00:55.680 --> 00:58.099
Want perfection? Me too, so keep
out of my way.

00:58.600 --> 01:00.685
WARM HAPPINESS IN MINUTES!
MATNA FOUR-MINUTE CURRY

01:00.769 --> 01:02.479
-Ah.
-So yummy!

01:02.562 --> 01:03.730
Dinner's taken care of!

01:04.731 --> 01:05.899
Dinner's taken care of!

01:08.151 --> 01:09.235
EUNSUNG SUPER VACUUM

01:10.403 --> 01:13.364
-You're a lifesaver, Eunsung!
-You're a lifesaver, Eunsung!

01:37.180 --> 01:38.014
Mom.

01:38.890 --> 01:42.519
Ye-jin! Ye-jin, are you ok? Are you hurt?

01:47.899 --> 01:54.739
Dad, this is my mom, right? Right?
She's my mom, right?

01:58.785 --> 01:59.619
Mom.

02:00.161 --> 02:05.792
It's me. Dam Seok-gyeong. Ye-jin's
struggling. Please, just meet her once.

02:13.466 --> 02:14.300
Ye-jin.

02:17.095 --> 02:19.806
It's me, mom. Darling, come here.

02:23.768 --> 02:24.602
Mom!

02:29.107 --> 02:32.944
I'm sorry. I'm sorry, baby. I am so
sorry.

02:44.706 --> 02:46.958
-Do you like it? Is it tasty?
-It's so tasty!

03:10.940 --> 03:15.403
Mom. Next time, can we play outside?

03:20.533 --> 03:23.411
I want to go with you to an amusement
park too.

03:24.871 --> 03:27.832
Uh… Mom's a busy bee, so…

03:27.916 --> 03:28.750
Then…

03:29.584 --> 03:31.502
when will I see you again, mom?

03:40.511 --> 03:44.474
Ye-jin, take this. It's my phone number,
yeah? Whenever, you miss me, call this

03:44.557 --> 03:45.433
number.

03:47.685 --> 03:48.519
Really?

03:48.603 --> 03:52.357
In return, can you please promise
one thing to me? You must wait until

03:52.440 --> 03:59.364
I come to see you, Ye-jin. Wait, please.
Don't come and look for me. Ever.

04:08.248 --> 04:09.123
Well, it's because…

04:09.207 --> 04:11.042
It's our little secret.

04:20.510 --> 04:25.390
Can I call you each day? Oh. You're busy.
I forgot.

04:26.933 --> 04:29.644
Well then, how about this? At eight pm
on Sundays, you call me to chat.

04:29.727 --> 04:36.693
I'll make sure to pick up no matter what.
Hello, Ye-jin.

04:37.652 --> 04:40.738
I won, mom! I'm president. Almost
everybody voted for me.

04:40.822 --> 04:42.949
Wow! Congratulations!

04:43.032 --> 04:45.034
A LOVE LIKE MOSS

04:50.665 --> 04:52.667
EUN-SU'S LAW

04:54.043 --> 04:55.837
SHE IS AMAZING
SHEER PERFECTION

04:55.920 --> 04:58.631
TOTALLY MY KIND OF ACTRESS
CAN'T WAIT FOR HER NEXT WORK

04:58.715 --> 05:00.008
MOM

05:02.176 --> 05:05.722
Mom, do you make everyone pay?
Oh come on, can you please tell me?

05:06.222 --> 05:08.599
Nope, watch when it airs, okay?

05:09.892 --> 05:10.893
Ms. Song.

05:11.436 --> 05:14.814
Someone needs me. Let's talk longer next
week.

05:15.315 --> 05:16.316
Okay, love you, Mom.

05:26.284 --> 05:28.995
The number you have dialed is not
available.

05:34.751 --> 05:36.836
No way. Song Myeong-hwa was in an
accident.

05:36.919 --> 05:38.046
Really? What happened?

05:43.259 --> 05:46.137
SONG MYEONG-HWA IN CRITICAL
CONDITION AFTER CAR COLLISION

06:03.321 --> 06:05.740
We need to address the misinformation
right away.

06:05.823 --> 06:07.617
Song Myeong-hwa. Song Myeong-hwa. How did
you get injured?

06:07.700 --> 06:09.494
Song Myeong-hwa. Song Myeong-hwa,
when are you planning to come back

06:09.577 --> 06:10.411
on air?

06:10.495 --> 06:12.872
Was the accident premeditated, Song
Myeong-Hwa?

06:16.084 --> 06:16.918
Do you know her?

06:21.506 --> 06:24.008
-I mean…
-Are we allowing just anybody in here?

06:25.259 --> 06:28.346
-Sorry, but she needs to rest right now.
-No, no, no. Please answer our question!

06:28.429 --> 06:29.430
Get out, you're just bothering her,

06:29.514 --> 06:31.557
-miss. Come this way. Let's get this
-Get her picture.

06:31.641 --> 06:34.394
Random girl out of here. She's
bothering Ms. Song.

06:34.477 --> 06:39.732
Mom, I'm sorry. Will you please pick up,
just once.

06:43.194 --> 06:45.071
Mom, please just pick up, just once.

06:47.698 --> 06:48.533
Come on, please…

06:48.616 --> 06:51.369
The number you have dialed is temporarily
unavailable…

06:51.452 --> 06:52.995
Just this once.

06:54.247 --> 06:55.081
Mom,

06:57.583 --> 06:59.127
you took forever to answer.

07:12.390 --> 07:13.599
Are you listening?

07:18.980 --> 07:20.398
You've got the wrong number.

07:27.488 --> 07:28.322
You there?

07:30.408 --> 07:31.242
Hello?

07:59.061 --> 07:59.896
Mom?

08:02.356 --> 08:04.400
-Mom?
-If you call me one more time,

08:04.484 --> 08:07.820
I'll take this to the cops, alright?
Don't make me warn you again.

08:52.281 --> 08:53.950
-Hello.
-I miss you.

08:58.996 --> 09:00.414
I miss you so much.

09:03.459 --> 09:04.293
Mom.

09:56.971 --> 09:59.765
-Stop pushing me, Bun Hong! You've got
-Scoot over, I can't see anything.

09:59.849 --> 10:01.517
-Plenty of space. Put that away, look
-You're in my way Nan Sun, move to

10:01.601 --> 10:02.435
-here-- Oh hello!
-the right,

10:02.518 --> 10:04.437
Why, look who's here, our regulars.
Bright and early.

10:04.520 --> 10:06.480
Hello there! Jin-yi, I need a new butt.

10:08.107 --> 10:09.817
I also need a new butt please.

10:09.900 --> 10:10.735
Butts?

10:11.527 --> 10:14.697
-Alright, then. A tall one just for you,
-Wow. A tall butt.

10:14.780 --> 10:19.076
-My dear. And for Nan Sun, a little one.
-Thank you, dear.

10:19.160 --> 10:22.705
Now don't go and swap your cushions
because you're besties, yeah? Use butts

10:22.788 --> 10:25.374
that match your height, so your knees
stay healthy.

10:26.751 --> 10:31.088
I think I'll buy a butt too. So Jin-yi
can pamper my poor knees as well.

10:31.922 --> 10:34.008
Why would you buy one, though?

10:34.091 --> 10:35.176
Give me one.

10:35.676 --> 10:36.802
No, save your money.

10:37.803 --> 10:39.847
-Aw, Jin-Yi.
-Now, Jin-yi is a true woman of business.

10:39.930 --> 10:41.599
She watches out for her people.

10:41.682 --> 10:43.351
Like our very own Robin Hood.

10:44.018 --> 10:46.187
Let's go now. See you, Jin-yi!

10:46.270 --> 10:47.772
-Okay, see you.
-We should go.

10:47.855 --> 10:50.191
Come on, let's get some coffee. The cafe
should be open.

10:50.274 --> 10:51.400
Be safe! Enjoy your day!

10:51.484 --> 10:54.403
Oh, Na Som-yi,
wait, wait, wait, wait. Let's see.

10:55.946 --> 11:01.535
Okay. Okay. Breathe in. All set.
Here you go.

11:03.954 --> 11:05.456
Ugh, what is it?

11:05.539 --> 11:08.084
It's a special mask woven with a
rare Punggi Viscose Rayon for you,

11:08.167 --> 11:13.172
Som-yi. It's light and doesn't make you
sweat. Soft and smooth. Cool, yeah?

11:13.255 --> 11:15.508
Forget it. I'll just use the one I have.

11:16.092 --> 11:18.177
Four, three, two.

11:19.470 --> 11:20.930
Oh, come on!

11:30.398 --> 11:31.232
How is it?

11:33.734 --> 11:35.319
-Meh. I don't know.
-Hm.

11:36.529 --> 11:37.530
Na Som-yi.

11:39.782 --> 11:40.616
Huh?

11:43.619 --> 11:50.126
Wow! No way! I've really had my eye
on this! Okay, which angel did this?

11:50.626 --> 11:53.587
Hae-sook, who else? Hey! Did you beg him
again?

11:54.463 --> 11:58.300
Nuh-uh. I'm gonna come back later and
open it, so hold on to it for me.

11:59.969 --> 12:00.886
Keep going.

12:00.970 --> 12:03.305
-Hello.
-Keep going, sweetie.

12:34.754 --> 12:39.467
Ugh, my eyes are so puffy? How much
soup did I have yesterday?

12:48.100 --> 12:48.934
Heading out?

12:49.018 --> 12:51.270
Huh? Yes. Are you also on your way
out, ma'am?

12:51.353 --> 12:52.897
Yes, I'm going to the market.

12:52.980 --> 12:55.816
In that case, can I go with you? I'm also
hopping on the bus.

12:55.900 --> 12:57.985
Alright. I'll take you, come along.

12:58.068 --> 12:59.278
Do you still drive a car?

12:59.361 --> 13:02.573
Heavens, really? I have a stellar
chauffeur, he always drives me.

13:02.656 --> 13:04.033
It's great.

13:22.843 --> 13:26.263
What? Oh, oh, that's it! That's the one!
I'm telling you, this bird, was

13:26.347 --> 13:30.434
soaring above in the sky only yesterday!
You acted like I'm some petty thief and

13:30.518 --> 13:34.563
called the cops on me. Are you sure that
that's really a… that that is truly a

13:34.647 --> 13:40.528
chicken? I mean, she doesn't look a bit
off to you?

13:45.699 --> 13:47.368
Do you have nothing to say to me?

13:54.124 --> 13:54.959
Here you go.

14:02.383 --> 14:04.301
Not money for repairs. I meant that you
owe me an…

14:04.385 --> 14:05.344
Are we done here?

14:06.011 --> 14:07.888
I hope we never see each other again.

14:10.140 --> 14:10.975
Look here!

14:11.725 --> 14:12.810
What? What? What?

14:14.353 --> 14:15.354
Can we please talk?

14:16.939 --> 14:19.567
Come on or we'll miss the bus! Move it,
let's go!

14:24.780 --> 14:25.614
Ugh…

14:28.158 --> 14:30.369
So you can't move any of this stuff out?

14:30.452 --> 14:32.913
I can't. I'm only offering a spot to you,
ma'am.

14:34.331 --> 14:37.376
Come on, she'll just hop on my
lap and ride that way.

14:37.459 --> 14:40.504
You had knee surgery this past year.
I can't allow that.

14:41.213 --> 14:43.215
Get in, it's ok. I'll just walk over.

14:43.299 --> 14:45.050
Why can't she just join us?

14:45.134 --> 14:46.302
We're going to be late.

14:47.595 --> 14:51.223
Good grief. I'll handle it. Let's go.

14:52.182 --> 14:53.017
What…

14:53.100 --> 14:56.145
Sit. Sit. What a lovely pair! You look
wonderful together! Oh, do you

14:56.228 --> 14:57.688
got a fella?

15:00.691 --> 15:02.484
-What?
-Ma'am!

15:03.068 --> 15:05.988
Oh my dear, my poor knees are aching.
So I need to sit.

15:13.245 --> 15:14.413
Put your feet up there.

15:17.082 --> 15:17.917
Sure.

15:36.060 --> 15:39.813
No! Bees! There are bees! There, look,
bees! Are they still there? Are they

15:39.897 --> 15:41.190
still there?

15:42.149 --> 15:42.983
No ma'am.

15:48.697 --> 15:50.199
What the hell was their deal?

15:53.035 --> 15:53.869
I know, right?

16:02.586 --> 16:06.465
I'm sorry. For the misunderstanding
yesterday. I went too far.

16:09.051 --> 16:12.763
I mean, I understand why it happened.
Let's just drop it. Oh, the money in

16:12.846 --> 16:19.770
the envelope. I placed it in your
trunk, don't forget to take it.

16:19.853 --> 16:21.063
I won't. I don't want it.

16:21.146 --> 16:22.606
I don't want it either, ok?

16:23.148 --> 16:24.358
You said it's expensive.

16:24.942 --> 16:27.611
Oh, please. I'm Dam Ye-jin, you know?

17:16.243 --> 17:17.286
Dam Ye-jin?

17:23.417 --> 17:24.501
Hurry up and get in.

17:31.842 --> 17:34.553
Just pay when you get off the bus Jesus,
granny!

17:34.636 --> 17:36.221
Oh no, it's not that, dear.

17:36.305 --> 17:37.139
Oh my God!

17:37.222 --> 17:40.768
You must be hungry. You probably
didn't even eat breakfast. You work

17:40.851 --> 17:43.812
so hard. Come on, please take it.

17:47.232 --> 17:49.818
Sang-geum dear, why did you give
him that?

18:14.802 --> 18:16.804
WE SPENT OUR TWENTIES TOGETHER…

18:20.641 --> 18:21.475
Whoa.

18:33.112 --> 18:33.946
Huh? Ae-ra!

18:41.620 --> 18:44.998
You know, we met when we were eight.
And now… We're forty and fine.

18:45.082 --> 18:48.919
Forty-fine. Forty, fresh, and fine.
Hey, Ae-ra. My next video for NeoTube is

18:49.002 --> 18:52.256
titled "Meet the local celebrities
from my neighborhood." I can't

18:52.339 --> 18:56.009
post without Moon Ae-ra making an
appearance though, obviously. Our class

18:56.093 --> 19:03.016
president, top student, and
ultimate playground boss, am I right?

19:04.601 --> 19:05.561
Are you that bored?

19:06.186 --> 19:09.523
Walk to the macaroon spot with me
and I'll film you looking amazing.

19:09.606 --> 19:12.151
Come on, you'll love it, trust me.
In or out?

19:13.902 --> 19:16.864
Let's see. Remind me again, how many
subscribers do you have?

19:16.947 --> 19:17.948
Sev… en.

19:23.120 --> 19:24.830
How about when I hit ten followers?

19:24.913 --> 19:26.582
-Are you crazy? Go away.
-A dozen?

19:26.665 --> 19:27.833
Come on, twenty.

19:29.001 --> 19:32.713
The product that I, Park Kwang-Mo,
captain and ultimate lover of Deokpung,

19:32.796 --> 19:36.800
will be reporting on is… a plastic bottle
windmill that makes moles say bye-bye!

19:36.884 --> 19:39.803
It's a cost-saving tool, a miraculously
powerful repellent.

19:39.887 --> 19:43.348
The breeze moves the bottles! The plastic
bottles spin around, you see.

19:43.432 --> 19:47.060
The vibration travels underground
Moles sense them. They flee and think,

19:47.144 --> 19:50.522
oh my, oh no, it must be an earthquake
happening. It's so simple to

19:50.606 --> 19:54.359
install, and dirt cheap. I'm floored.
And speak of the devil, our true hero

19:54.443 --> 19:58.572
of the village has joined the segment.
It's Mechoori!

20:00.532 --> 20:04.286
Here he comes! He's moving this way!
He should stop any second now. For all

20:04.369 --> 20:11.293
the love and support you've shown to Park
Kwang… Hey! hey! Hey, Mechoori!

20:18.342 --> 20:21.929
Sheeh, what were you thinking, dozing off
while driving in the paddies?

20:22.512 --> 20:24.097
I'm sleeping a lot less lately.

20:25.015 --> 20:27.768
Why's that though? Mosquitoes
bothering you?

20:28.644 --> 20:31.396
No, I'm bothered by persistent species.

20:32.022 --> 20:34.107
Huh? What's that?

20:35.817 --> 20:37.569
Mom. Mom. Mom.

20:41.865 --> 20:42.699
Mom.

20:43.951 --> 20:49.289
Just go home and rest up today. I'll look
over it all. I can handle all that.

20:49.915 --> 20:51.625
Okay, thank you so much, Kwang-mo.

20:57.172 --> 20:58.757
Ah, the weather is so nice.

21:04.346 --> 21:05.430
What's going on here?

21:08.892 --> 21:11.603
-Huh?
-Mechoori. What's that?

21:16.275 --> 21:18.694
Hey guys, don't forget to carry this over
there.

21:19.903 --> 21:22.948
Move that over there. Please hurry
up as much as you can.

21:23.031 --> 21:23.865
Oh, okay.

21:31.248 --> 21:33.208
Hyung, come out.

21:36.295 --> 21:37.129
Hae Seok.

21:47.222 --> 21:48.056
Explain, please.

21:48.140 --> 21:51.059
What do you mean? It's obvious, we're
preparing to begin construction.

21:51.143 --> 21:52.728
It's for your lab, of course.

21:52.811 --> 21:54.855
That's messed up, you could've told me
about it.

21:54.938 --> 21:58.025
I would have but you changed your number
so I couldn't tell you beforehand. Yeah.

21:58.108 --> 22:02.029
I was trying to do it while you were away
at the farm.

22:02.112 --> 22:03.613
I told you before it's a no.

22:05.866 --> 22:09.453
Are you gonna be here just farming alone
forever? Is that really the life you

22:09.536 --> 22:11.580
-wanted?
-Yeah.

22:11.663 --> 22:15.334
Yeah right. You're only truly happy
in a lab and experimenting.

22:19.671 --> 22:21.715
-We did it! We did it!
-No way! We did it!

22:21.798 --> 22:22.632
We did it!

22:23.133 --> 22:25.927
We did it! We did it. Finally. Finally!

22:26.470 --> 22:29.181
I heard Chang-ho's been really
successful in Bangkok. He says he's

22:29.264 --> 22:32.351
actually more cut out for business than
a lab. But what about you? Will you

22:32.434 --> 22:33.977
stay shut off like this forever?

22:34.061 --> 22:36.688
I'm happy with things as they are.
I told you that.

22:36.772 --> 22:39.816
Just wait for it. Our lab's gonna produce
a mega hit product that will transform

22:39.900 --> 22:41.193
the entire country.

22:41.276 --> 22:42.527
Hey, hey!

22:43.153 --> 22:44.404
Why are you doing that?

22:44.946 --> 22:45.781
Hey!

22:51.036 --> 22:53.997
-You need to move that over there, man.
-Sir, hold on, look over here! Can you

22:54.081 --> 22:55.749
-please stop?
-What?

22:55.832 --> 22:57.834
Hold it for a moment. Why don't
you take a break?

22:57.918 --> 22:59.503
-Huh?
-And come back later? Okay, thanks.

22:59.586 --> 23:01.630
-Ok.
-Stop working for now.

23:04.508 --> 23:08.220
I can't believe you're doing this to me.
Do you even know how many calls I

23:08.303 --> 23:12.140
received from L'Etoile today alone? Huh?
They keep calling.

23:16.728 --> 23:18.730
This is driving me crazy too you know.

23:22.025 --> 23:24.986
Meet them again and make it clear.
We're not gonna renew.

23:25.070 --> 23:28.657
Go ahead. I bet they'll give up in a
split second, just talk to them.

23:28.740 --> 23:29.866
Go ahead.

23:37.249 --> 23:38.083
What? Hey.

23:39.584 --> 23:40.419
Speaking.

23:45.048 --> 23:47.634
-Huh? Why are you still here? Oh, go
-I was just about to leave. Ok.

23:47.717 --> 23:48.552
Ahead.

23:52.097 --> 23:53.056
Hey man, seriously?

23:54.558 --> 23:57.644
You… still don't really know who I am,
huh?

24:00.147 --> 24:03.108
Kang Mo-won, sir. Kang Mu-won!

24:08.363 --> 24:10.574
I can't allow you to look so
unprofessional.

24:24.379 --> 24:25.213
All done.

24:54.868 --> 24:58.246
Sir, how come you've never before shown
me… such a perfect suit?

24:58.747 --> 25:02.125
Actually, you two are wearing… the same
exact suit.

25:02.626 --> 25:03.460
What?

25:18.558 --> 25:19.392
Bravo!

25:24.314 --> 25:25.982
Wow, get out of here.

25:29.945 --> 25:31.738
Stop, boss. It's blinding my eyes.

25:35.408 --> 25:39.120
Yeah, it's too much, let's not.
I told you I don't need it.

25:39.204 --> 25:40.539
Ugh, just go in this, okay?

25:40.622 --> 25:41.456
Hey.

25:42.040 --> 25:43.458
Why can't I just grab a taxi?

25:43.542 --> 25:46.461
Pay attention. In business, all things
like this are a power play. No matter

25:46.545 --> 25:49.756
how well you fight, you can't win a
battle with bare hands…

25:50.423 --> 25:51.758
At this rate, I'm going to be late.

25:51.841 --> 25:53.051
Take that off, wear this.

25:53.134 --> 25:54.094
Hyung.

25:55.303 --> 25:57.764
Alright, then will you please just go in
the car?

26:12.112 --> 26:15.949
It's nice to meet you. I'm co-CEO
of Gojeuneok Bio. Lee Hae-seok, sir.

26:16.032 --> 26:18.618
It's a true pleasure. I'm L'Etoile's CEO,
Eric Seo.

26:21.621 --> 26:24.666
I admit that the amount of raw material
from the previous order was unreasonable

26:24.749 --> 26:27.669
on our end. Our updated terms in the
contract indicate a gradual increase of

26:27.752 --> 26:30.171
the raw materials. We've also
included clauses stipulating that

26:30.255 --> 26:33.258
we will cover all of you company's fees
for hiring more employees and expanding

26:33.341 --> 26:35.218
its facilities.

26:36.344 --> 26:38.888
I think you may not totally
understand why we rejected renewing the

26:38.972 --> 26:39.848
contract.

26:40.348 --> 26:44.603
For us independence is essential.
We want to operate fully in-house, sir.

26:45.353 --> 26:48.148
I refuse to team up with any company that
goes against that principle.

26:48.231 --> 26:51.234
Well, I believe you'll have that after
improving your facilities and manpower.

26:51.318 --> 26:54.029
But that alone can't promise the
quality of the raw materials.

26:54.112 --> 26:56.990
Isn't your ultimate wish to have a
better product for much more people, Mr.

26:57.073 --> 26:57.907
Lee?

26:59.034 --> 27:00.285
What if my wish is a mistake?

27:00.368 --> 27:01.828
It can still bring hope.

27:05.040 --> 27:08.001
Hope can help… at least in theory, but
alone, it's careless. It doesn't accept

27:08.084 --> 27:10.795
responsibility. If you have that kind of
blind optimism, that's another

27:10.879 --> 27:14.090
reason not to collaborate.

27:15.842 --> 27:18.428
How about this, let's say we only
request the same amount as the old

27:18.511 --> 27:19.429
contract?

27:19.512 --> 27:21.765
I hear you're preparing to launch your
products at HIT.

27:21.848 --> 27:23.683
We're selling a limited supply to their
company.

27:23.767 --> 27:26.227
But they'll demand more. They'll put
pressure for more and fast.

27:26.311 --> 27:29.356
There's no future with someone who
backtracks on agr---

27:32.817 --> 27:33.652
agreements.

27:39.407 --> 27:42.535
I think you understand me clearly now.
So I'll be heading out.

27:45.121 --> 27:48.833
Are you sure? We're not just any brand.

27:58.760 --> 28:00.887
Maybe I should've kept out that last
part.

28:06.810 --> 28:08.728
You said you had something very urgent?

28:08.812 --> 28:12.399
I do have something indeed. Turns out
that Gojeuneok Bio has a co-CEO. Kang

28:12.482 --> 28:16.319
Mu-won. And also, Lee Hae-seok.

28:17.696 --> 28:18.530
Lee Hae-seok?

28:18.613 --> 28:22.492
It's Mr. Lee that has final authority
with contract renewal. He's firm on not

28:22.575 --> 28:23.702
renewing.

28:23.785 --> 28:25.954
You met with Hae-seok? Tell me
where he is.

28:26.955 --> 28:28.998
He's not someone that you can really meet
that easily.

28:29.082 --> 28:32.085
Not him too, really? The farm owner is
just like that. I came back empty-handed

28:32.168 --> 28:34.629
from there too many times.

28:35.213 --> 28:39.384
Gojeuneok Bio seems to be run by people
with similar minds and sensibilities.

28:42.429 --> 28:45.515
Ok. Let's start Plan B, Mr. Seo.
If they're coming in a pair,

28:45.598 --> 28:49.477
we should too. I'll work on convincing
the CEO Mr. Lee from now on.

28:53.481 --> 28:54.315
Sound good?

28:57.986 --> 29:03.908
Really? Do you really not recognize me?
Do you really not remember me?

29:08.204 --> 29:09.038
I do.

29:10.749 --> 29:14.711
Did you just say you remember me?
Then why pretend otherwise?

29:16.254 --> 29:20.300
I felt sorry. I felt so bad that I
couldn't… see you on that day.

29:21.551 --> 29:25.388
You mean… you never came that day because
you weren't able to? Did something

29:25.472 --> 29:26.347
happen?

29:28.975 --> 29:30.393
It was so long ago, you see?

29:31.686 --> 29:35.273
Ah, well. We could talk until
you remember that day, don't you think?

29:36.691 --> 29:37.525
Mr. Seo.

29:39.736 --> 29:41.946
Alright, let's go with your Plan B then.

29:46.284 --> 29:49.204
Can't we just find a new raw materials
supplier elsewhere?

29:49.704 --> 29:52.916
Uh, I actually spoke to headquarters
about that. They took the white

29:52.999 --> 29:56.127
flower noori mushrooms and tried to
cultivate them in France. But they

29:56.211 --> 29:59.172
failed. And even if they
succeeded, they're prohibited from

29:59.255 --> 30:02.550
selling the mushroom because
Gojeuneok holds an exclusive patent.

30:02.634 --> 30:06.137
So in conclusion, we have no other option
but Gojeuneok. What about the farm

30:06.221 --> 30:07.055
owner? Huh?

30:07.138 --> 30:11.100
Mission impossible. I failed to even
meet him. One of the workers at the farm

30:11.184 --> 30:15.146
said the owner's an antagonizing person.
He seems to be extremely closed off to

30:15.230 --> 30:16.231
outsiders.

30:17.982 --> 30:23.947
These two people. Don't they seem almost
identical? Oh! What if they are the same?

30:24.447 --> 30:25.990
-Whoa.
-Wow, Mr. Huang

30:26.491 --> 30:27.617
You know?

30:27.700 --> 30:29.244
Whoa, we're in the company of a genius.

30:29.327 --> 30:30.286
Is he the best we can do?

30:30.370 --> 30:32.038
-I don't think so.
-That's too bad.

30:32.121 --> 30:32.956
Just fire him.

30:33.039 --> 30:35.375
Can we really rule out the possibility
though?

30:35.875 --> 30:39.254
Come on. How could one person look after
the farm and also run the company?

30:39.337 --> 30:42.215
Does he have super powers to be
everywhere at once? We're living

30:42.298 --> 30:45.218
in a world where being good at just
one thing is hard enough! I'm

30:45.301 --> 30:46.761
struggling so much right now.

30:53.101 --> 30:55.103
ANYOUNG PUNGMI RICE

30:58.606 --> 31:02.569
Yeah. Anyway, let me know if you have an
opening. Thanks. There's no such thing

31:02.652 --> 31:07.949
as a break when you're strapped for
money man.

31:08.449 --> 31:09.617
Okay, got it.

31:37.353 --> 31:38.563
Use this for milk money.

31:45.570 --> 31:47.655
-You're home already.
-Yeah. Hey.

31:47.739 --> 31:48.823
Why aren't you coming in?

31:48.907 --> 31:50.199
It's nothing. It's nothing.

31:50.283 --> 31:52.160
Get inside. Hey, did you order rice?

31:52.243 --> 31:53.244
No, I didn't.

31:53.328 --> 31:55.538
Oh, Se-jung, did you have fun playing
today?

31:55.622 --> 31:58.082
DEOKPUNG VILLAGE
WHERE WIND STOPS TO TAKE A BREAK

32:26.402 --> 32:28.279
Sorry for everything.

32:31.074 --> 32:34.827
Because I struggled to make ends meet
recently.

32:36.162 --> 32:38.539
I forgot how to treat people
with decency.

32:38.623 --> 32:42.919
I thought I was alone in this world,
so I did a lot of embarrassing things.

32:46.005 --> 32:49.759
From now on, I'll leave right on time.
And I won't speed either. Should you

32:49.842 --> 32:53.805
need to use the bathroom before we leave,
feel free to tell me and I'll be sure

32:53.888 --> 32:54.889
to wait.

32:58.267 --> 33:00.561
-Goodness, thank you.
-I'm so happy to hear this, thank you

33:00.645 --> 33:01.479
young man!

33:01.562 --> 33:02.480
What a lovely man.

33:02.563 --> 33:05.483
Thank you. We appreciate you, young man.

33:07.485 --> 33:08.319
Thank you, sir.

33:23.543 --> 33:26.379
Please, think of it as saving a
person's life here. Just this once.

33:26.462 --> 33:27.922
I'm asking you just this once.

33:28.006 --> 33:30.800
-Oh, I told you, I'm just extremely…
-Oh please.

33:31.342 --> 33:32.343
Super busy right now, miss.

33:32.427 --> 33:36.055
We just get so many people watching when
you're on the segment, Ms. Dam!

33:38.349 --> 33:41.269
Hi there, HIT members. This is your
home shopping host, Dam Ye-jin. Welcome!

33:41.352 --> 33:42.186
Today, I'll be here working as a

33:42.270 --> 33:43.104
HIT CALL SERVICE CENTER

33:43.187 --> 33:43.938
call center agent so I can help and

33:44.022 --> 33:46.315
hear about the inconveniences
our customers are experiencing

33:46.399 --> 33:49.110
currently. I'll be here answering
directly to you all. Let's get to it.

33:49.193 --> 33:53.406
Hello,ma'am. You're speaking with…

33:55.992 --> 33:58.411
Um, about the shampoo that's on
right now… I'll buy half of the

33:58.494 --> 34:01.330
number one package at half price.

34:01.414 --> 34:05.334
Ahh. Sorry ma'am, but I'm not able to
change the components of your package

34:05.418 --> 34:06.544
or the price.

34:07.879 --> 34:10.923
Huh! Why would I buy a shampoo
that I won't use? Aren't you encouraging

34:11.007 --> 34:12.091
overconsumption then?

34:13.134 --> 34:15.344
Good afternoon, ma'am. How may I
help you?

34:15.428 --> 34:17.680
Hello, I'd like to return the galbitang.

34:17.764 --> 34:20.892
Okay, may I ask if there is
something wrong with this product?

34:20.975 --> 34:22.643
I sampled it, but I didn't
really like it.

34:22.727 --> 34:25.688
So you sampled the galbitang and you
didn't find the flavor to be as nice for…

34:25.772 --> 34:26.606
No,

34:26.689 --> 34:29.400
I ate all of them. But they didn't taste
so good. And those bones were

34:29.484 --> 34:32.361
too big too. You know, my dear, they were
so heavy.

34:32.445 --> 34:34.489
But if you ate them, I'm not sure how
you plan to…

34:34.572 --> 34:37.450
I ate them, okay! I ate them and I
didn't leave any!

34:37.950 --> 34:38.951
Hello, this is…

34:39.035 --> 34:40.828
-Take responsibility.
-What?

34:44.373 --> 34:45.875
How can I help you today, sir?

34:46.417 --> 34:49.253
Look, my family's in shambles
just because of these damn golf shoes!

34:49.337 --> 34:52.757
I see you ordered a pair of the
women's golf shoes in a seven and a half.

34:52.840 --> 34:55.635
I mean, what kind of golf shoes are
delivered early at dawn? The wife saw

34:55.718 --> 34:58.638
everything! I mean, seriously! Are you
kidding? And now I'm going to divorce

34:58.721 --> 35:01.766
court at this old age. I'll have to pay
alimony and all that, so HIT should take

35:01.849 --> 35:03.267
responsibility and compensate me for…

35:03.351 --> 35:04.185
Sorry?

35:05.436 --> 35:06.479
What the?

35:09.065 --> 35:10.691
People really are the worst.

35:10.775 --> 35:12.819
Excuse me, Ms. Dam.

35:13.903 --> 35:16.989
Please, could you maybe… just take one
call without any issues?

35:17.073 --> 35:17.907
Yes, please.

35:17.990 --> 35:20.076
Okay. I'm sorry.

35:23.037 --> 35:26.582
I'll do it, just watch me kill it.
I'm Dam Yes-yes from now on.

35:26.666 --> 35:27.667
-Yes, yes.
-Yes, yes.

35:27.750 --> 35:30.962
Yes, yes. Yes, yes. Yes, yes. We've got
a caller right now. Let's jump right in.

35:31.045 --> 35:34.340
Hello, sir. This is Dam Ye-jin, your
customer service representative.

35:34.423 --> 35:35.299
HIT, yes?

35:35.383 --> 35:36.342
Yes, that's right.

35:36.425 --> 35:38.469
How could you sell this piece of junk?

35:39.220 --> 35:42.974
Ah… Sorry, is there some sort of issue
with the product?

35:43.724 --> 35:47.103
Doesn't HIT have quality control?
How could you ship a product that's

35:47.186 --> 35:50.481
so bogus it doesn't work? How could
you get something this wrong?

35:51.065 --> 35:53.067
You're using that as a drying rack?

35:53.151 --> 35:56.279
Oh it's fine, it's not like it's
heating up much at all, anyway.

35:56.362 --> 35:57.238
Why, is it broken?

35:57.321 --> 36:01.701
It was so expensive after all. Good lord.

36:04.162 --> 36:07.123
I don't know what it is but it's an
expensive piece of furniture.

36:07.206 --> 36:09.792
Oh. You bought the product because you
trusted Dam Ye-jin. But there

36:09.876 --> 36:11.627
was something wrong with it.

36:11.711 --> 36:14.839
I never trusted Dam Ye-jin. But still.
I'm very disappointed.

36:14.922 --> 36:18.551
I see. Could you please hold for a
second.

36:23.389 --> 36:26.893
Uh… excuse me, hello? Sir, could
you please tell me your name so I can

36:26.976 --> 36:29.770
find your purchase information?

36:32.398 --> 36:36.360
It's Lee Hae-seok. It's Lee Hae-seok.
It's Lee Hae-seok. It's Lee Hae-seok.

36:36.444 --> 36:39.822
Turns out that Gojeuneok Bio has a
co-CEO. Kang Mu-won and

36:40.364 --> 36:41.199
Lee Hae-seok.

36:41.282 --> 36:44.785
These two people. Don't they seem almost
identical? What if they're the same?

36:44.869 --> 36:47.538
Not him too, really? The farm owner is
just like that. I came back empty-handed

36:47.622 --> 36:49.665
from there too many times Is Lee
Redacted-Seok here? Lee Redacted-seok!

36:49.749 --> 36:52.126
I don't know your full name. It was
blocked out to protect your privacy.

36:52.210 --> 36:53.628
-What's your name?
-Matthew.

36:55.671 --> 36:57.256
Turns out that Gojeuneok Bio has a
co-CEO.

36:57.340 --> 36:58.633
The farm owner… I've got a delivery for…

36:58.716 --> 36:59.800
It's Lee Hae-seok.

37:01.260 --> 37:02.470
RAW MATERIALS
FARM OWNER

37:10.645 --> 37:13.356
It's Lee Hae-seok. It's Lee Hae-seok.

37:17.193 --> 37:20.863
Sir, could you please hold for just a
minute? Tell him that the person in

37:20.947 --> 37:23.783
charge plans to come there and
support him in person.

37:29.205 --> 37:35.086
I really, really appreciate it. Thank you
so much ladies! Yes!

37:38.214 --> 37:39.715
Let's do it.

37:43.678 --> 37:46.472
So do whatever you need to do to get
around, okay?

37:46.555 --> 37:47.640
Oh, no.

37:47.723 --> 37:49.809
I'm usually chased after by men in
sports cars,

37:49.892 --> 37:53.229
but being chased in a tractor is
something else. So points for that.

37:53.312 --> 37:56.857
So Mechoori is a nickname for…
for Matthew Lee! What an odd choice.

38:00.278 --> 38:01.529
Ugh, for God's sake.

38:05.658 --> 38:08.869
Ye-jin, you're crazy. What were
you thinking? You must be out of

38:08.953 --> 38:12.581
your mind. Alright. I'm gonna fix it.
Can I? Of course. I'm not sure I can.

38:12.665 --> 38:16.335
I can. I will. I'll do it. I must.
I got this. Where do I begin? I've got

38:16.419 --> 38:18.629
to start the car.

38:56.751 --> 39:00.129
Hello, there. We cross paths yet again.

39:07.887 --> 39:09.305
Did you forget our written agreement?

39:09.388 --> 39:11.640
I came because you called me, mister.

39:15.436 --> 39:17.646
Give me the contact of the person in
charge.

39:23.569 --> 39:24.528
HIT HOST
DAM YE-JIN

39:26.739 --> 39:27.573
I hope you're kidding.

39:27.656 --> 39:30.868
What? Why? I sold it, so… I am the
person in charge.

39:32.078 --> 39:34.330
Now, where's that half-bath device, sir?

39:35.831 --> 39:39.293
Alright. Fine. Come look at it, Ms. in
charge.

39:40.669 --> 39:43.172
Sure, absolutely. Here comes the person
in charge!

39:59.480 --> 40:02.733
Based on my inspection it's not
broken at all. You simply failed to

40:02.817 --> 40:04.652
operate it properly. Sir.

40:05.152 --> 40:07.279
-This package comes with a preheating
-That's not right.

40:07.363 --> 40:08.572
Blanket as well. Use the blanket

40:08.656 --> 40:09.698
Four-six-zero-six-two-seven.

40:09.782 --> 40:11.742
-To cover it… press the power button…
-No, it's not.

40:11.826 --> 40:14.620
And preheat for twenty minutes. Let
me show you.

40:14.703 --> 40:16.872
Take a look at this. It's a blanket.

40:17.373 --> 40:20.459
I said to cover the lid with it,
before you pre-heat it. It seems you

40:20.543 --> 40:22.962
were not paying attention when I
explained that.

40:25.005 --> 40:26.590
What's the point of even arguing
about it?

40:26.674 --> 40:29.468
What do you mean, argue? Come on, do you
think I included this blanket to

40:29.552 --> 40:32.471
cook soup with or something?

40:33.556 --> 40:36.725
Are you acting this way because
you realize the machine was perfectly

40:36.809 --> 40:39.395
fine and now you're embarrassed.
That's it, oh wow.

40:40.271 --> 40:42.064
She said it barely even heats up!

40:44.567 --> 40:48.154
Let's settle this once and for all.
I'll show you it heats up properly!

40:48.237 --> 40:51.490
Let's open that too. So you can't
call and complain saying that's

40:51.574 --> 40:53.325
broken either.

40:55.411 --> 40:57.121
Well, then, why don't you open it?

40:59.081 --> 41:01.834
Can't you feel the heat? And it's
only just preheating.

41:02.710 --> 41:04.670
It's barely even making me hot.

41:05.921 --> 41:07.089
You sure about that?

41:11.051 --> 41:13.846
Stop, hold on. Why are you doing that?

41:14.388 --> 41:15.222
What?

41:15.306 --> 41:18.392
Right there. You're pressing an
acupuncture points. That's what's gonna

41:18.476 --> 41:20.478
make you sweat so much.

41:20.561 --> 41:23.355
Do you really think I sweat by just
massaging my temples? I'd open my own

41:23.439 --> 41:26.150
sauna. You're just embarrassed because I
told you about the blanket but

41:26.233 --> 41:27.401
you didn't listen.

41:33.741 --> 41:37.161
Oh! There! Sweat! There! I knew it!
You're sweating! There, there there.

41:37.244 --> 41:38.704
It's running down your cheek.

41:42.583 --> 41:43.918
Huh, I wonder, maybe it's the roof?

41:44.001 --> 41:45.753
No, the roof looks solid I think.

41:46.253 --> 41:49.965
Mr. Mechoori. Hey eyes on me! Not up
there. Mr. Mechoori. Look at my face.

41:50.049 --> 41:52.593
You see, your sweat is pooling
right here.

41:53.344 --> 41:55.054
This place heats up fast.

41:55.971 --> 41:58.057
Uh-huh. Put up your arms.

41:59.266 --> 42:00.476
-Huh?
-Put your arms up.

42:01.644 --> 42:02.478
Wh-why?

42:03.771 --> 42:05.397
-Okay.
-Huh?

42:05.898 --> 42:07.816
Mr. Mechoori, I'll take a quick look
at your arms.

42:07.900 --> 42:10.319
-Wh-why?
-Up, up, up. I just need to see something.

42:10.402 --> 42:11.445
Whoa! Why? What do you mean?

42:11.529 --> 42:13.781
Just do this! Put your arms up! Just for
a sec. Just do it.

42:13.864 --> 42:15.115
See what? What? Get away!

42:15.199 --> 42:17.326
-Lift your arms. Sit back down!
-Hey!

42:17.409 --> 42:19.328
No! Ms. Dam Ye-jin!

42:21.163 --> 42:23.165
-Ms. Dam Ye-jin! Stop!
-Yes, what is it?

42:24.250 --> 42:26.085
Alright, ok. I'll withdraw my complaint!

42:26.168 --> 42:28.128
No, it's too late. Not until I see
those pit stains.

42:28.212 --> 42:29.046
Ms. Dam Ye-jin!

43:01.036 --> 43:04.206
You must be really embarrassed.
Since you're serving me tea.

43:05.749 --> 43:08.669
How about you just go home, then?
Your work here is done.

43:09.795 --> 43:12.339
Are you seriously going to keep
denying it, Mechoori? Do you really

43:12.423 --> 43:15.175
think… I'd come all the way here
for only a defective product? HIT's got

43:15.259 --> 43:17.553
great customer service you know.

43:18.053 --> 43:20.097
It was you who overreacted and panicked.

43:20.180 --> 43:22.141
I just made a call to customer service.

43:23.100 --> 43:27.938
Exactly. And you really don't understand
why I overreacted?

43:30.941 --> 43:34.361
Allow me to introduce myself. Hello,
Mr. Lee.

43:39.408 --> 43:42.328
You'll see me again soon, Mr. Lee.

43:51.170 --> 43:54.006
Changsik. Good boy, aw.

43:58.093 --> 43:59.678
You're ignoring me too, huh?

44:01.889 --> 44:05.768
Paw. Hey, I'm really upset today. Paw.
Just once.

44:07.311 --> 44:13.776
Come on, just one time, Changsik. Paw.
Oh, come on now. One paw.

44:14.276 --> 44:15.194
Hey!

44:15.694 --> 44:16.654
Huh? Hi there.

44:16.737 --> 44:17.946
Give this to him.

44:21.283 --> 44:24.953
They say whether it's an animal or a man,
they've got to eat, before they

44:25.037 --> 44:28.499
can work. You should give him a
sweet snack to nibble on first if you

44:28.582 --> 44:30.042
want him to listen.

44:31.585 --> 44:37.675
True. I should bring him a snack.
Eat this, come on, boy.

44:42.471 --> 44:44.515
I wonder… what does he like?

44:46.600 --> 44:48.894
I almost forgot. The half bath you got.

44:49.812 --> 44:52.981
You know I got a call from Mechoori.
He said it's in top condition.

44:53.065 --> 44:55.609
What should we do? You came all the
way from Seoul?

44:55.693 --> 44:59.446
Oh! That was just one of many reasons.
Like those potatoes you made me.

45:00.280 --> 45:01.990
Let's boil some potatoes eh?

45:02.074 --> 45:06.620
Oh, if you're insisting on me sleeping
over, ma'am… Okay!

45:10.582 --> 45:11.542
FARMING JOURNAL

45:23.721 --> 45:25.806
HIT HOMESHOPPING
PROPOSAL FOR PARTNERSHIP

46:47.221 --> 46:48.263
You're awake?

46:49.181 --> 46:51.767
Oh, yes. Are you going somewhere?

46:51.850 --> 46:55.187
I'm going to the mushroom farm. They said
they need more hands.

46:56.939 --> 46:58.649
-Wait, where?
-The mushroom farm.

47:34.393 --> 47:35.227
Good morning.

47:36.186 --> 47:37.062
The weather's nice.

47:37.145 --> 47:38.272
-Sure is.
-Yeah.

47:38.355 --> 47:39.231
Oh, my.

47:39.314 --> 47:40.315
Hello.

47:40.399 --> 47:41.358
-Thank you!
-Hello.

47:41.441 --> 47:42.776
-Good morning.
-Hello.

47:42.860 --> 47:44.736
-Good morning.
-I did.

47:55.747 --> 47:56.582
Ms. Dam Ye-jin?

47:57.749 --> 47:58.625
How did you know?

48:00.878 --> 48:04.298
Oh my! I guess my looks aren't
something I can just hide with a pair of

48:04.381 --> 48:05.465
trousers.

48:08.385 --> 48:09.219
Am I right?

48:10.345 --> 48:13.432
This is your last warning. Leave. Now,
please.

48:13.974 --> 48:16.018
-Ah.
-Sweetie, come over here.

48:16.101 --> 48:18.478
Yes, ma'am! Oh, she's calling me, so…

48:18.979 --> 48:20.063
I mean. Oh.

48:20.772 --> 48:22.149
Your sweetie is on her way!

48:28.530 --> 48:33.869
The pride and joy of Deokpung! Deokpung's
own treasure! The white flower noori

48:33.952 --> 48:39.291
mushroom! Once more, treat each
person and flower, with the utmost

48:39.374 --> 48:42.002
love and respect here! Let's go!

48:42.085 --> 48:45.672
-Let's go. Let's do this!
-Let's do this!

49:04.608 --> 49:06.401
We'll get off work right on the dot
today!

49:06.485 --> 49:08.028
Of course, we will! Good thing, too!

49:08.111 --> 49:10.572
-Right on the dot!
-Our work is not finished yet. Deokpung's…

49:10.656 --> 49:12.407
Why? Let's go.

49:12.491 --> 49:14.534
-Let's go!
-Please finish up for me.

49:16.370 --> 49:19.623
Thank you for today! Thank you. Let's go.

49:26.880 --> 49:27.714
Good work.

49:29.007 --> 49:29.841
Thanks.

49:34.179 --> 49:37.766
Given all I've done, give me just a
moment of your day. Did you look at

49:37.849 --> 49:39.601
the documents I left for you?

49:40.811 --> 49:41.645
No.

49:42.270 --> 49:46.316
Ten minutes. Uh, ok, ok. Five. Just five
minutes. I'll brief you.

49:46.400 --> 49:47.442
No, thank you.

49:47.526 --> 49:50.779
Please, could you… reconsider
renewing the contract? L'Etoile

49:50.862 --> 49:54.491
says they only want to take as much
as Gojeuneok can produce. So there's

49:54.574 --> 49:55.701
no problems anymore.

49:55.784 --> 49:59.287
The trust's already been broken. We can't
partner with a company that's gone

49:59.371 --> 50:00.831
back on their word before.

50:00.914 --> 50:02.332
Are you an alien?

50:02.916 --> 50:05.377
Business is conducted by people.
You can't expect perfection from

50:05.460 --> 50:07.129
-everyone…
-Dam Ye-jin.

50:09.006 --> 50:11.675
You spill some water. Can you put it back
in the cup?

50:12.300 --> 50:15.012
I'm saying we should… clean it
quickly with a towel. And then hang that

50:15.095 --> 50:18.890
towel to dry. We could even reuse it
if we wring it out first.

50:18.974 --> 50:21.810
But neglecting to properly dry it…
brings mold, brings contamination.

50:21.893 --> 50:23.603
Do you get that?

50:29.192 --> 50:32.654
I understand where you're coming from.
But Mr. Lee, if you could just

50:32.738 --> 50:35.949
reconsider… Mr. Lee, I'm trying
my best to convince you, please.

50:36.033 --> 50:39.619
If we could just talk a little more,
you might change your mind. Oh no,

50:39.703 --> 50:42.164
my hand! You almost got it caught.

50:46.209 --> 50:49.588
If you take even one step inside,
I'm gonna call the police.

50:55.135 --> 50:55.969
Ms. Dam Ye-jin!

50:56.470 --> 50:59.681
Come on. We enjoyed a little sauna
together. And now you're being mean.

50:59.765 --> 51:00.599
Go away, please!

51:01.892 --> 51:03.226
Alright, I'll go very soon…

51:03.310 --> 51:04.352
What are you doing?

51:04.436 --> 51:07.272
I'll leave, but only if you talk to
me a little. Oh, you're putting weight

51:07.355 --> 51:08.190
-on it?
-Hey!

51:08.273 --> 51:12.152
-You're the one that's pushing right now.
-I mean, hold on a second, Mr. Lee.

51:12.235 --> 51:13.070
Ms. Dam Ye-jin!

51:13.153 --> 51:14.488
Mr. Lee, Mr. Lee. Mr. Lee!

51:22.204 --> 51:23.497
CHINESE CHARACTER
FOR "PERSON"

51:23.580 --> 51:26.333
IT IS A PICTOGRAM OF TWO PEOPLE LEANING
ONTO EACH OTHER

51:31.338 --> 51:32.172
Get off me.

51:35.467 --> 51:36.802
No, don't come inside. Get out!

51:36.885 --> 51:38.553
Ugh, I will, okay?

51:39.846 --> 51:40.931
Ugh, seriously.

51:58.031 --> 51:58.865
Ms. Dam Ye-jin.

52:03.078 --> 52:04.079
Ah, it hurts.

52:10.836 --> 52:14.673
I mean, it's not that I don't understand
your decision. That's why I want it

52:14.756 --> 52:18.426
even more. An essence derived from
raw materials. I would love to show my

52:18.510 --> 52:19.344
customers.

52:21.138 --> 52:24.141
Oh god, even my mouth is in pain
from talking so much alone.

52:27.269 --> 52:28.353
Enough, just quit it.

52:28.436 --> 52:31.064
Oh, my arm is in pain. What if I
can't use it again?

52:32.566 --> 52:33.692
It hurts so much.

52:35.443 --> 52:40.448
There, all done. Be careful to avoid
water, it can't get wet.

52:40.991 --> 52:43.535
Could I take it off tonight for
just a bit and then put it back

52:43.618 --> 52:44.494
on when I'm done?

52:45.370 --> 52:46.204
Excuse me?

52:47.289 --> 52:49.291
WOORI DEOKPUNG
MEDICAL CLINIC

52:54.671 --> 52:57.841
Why did you fall over like some drama
queen? Is this a kind of staged

52:57.924 --> 52:59.009
injury scam?

53:00.677 --> 53:04.431
You really think I would stoop this low
just to make you feel guilty? But I

53:04.514 --> 53:07.601
could try something else?

53:13.481 --> 53:17.235
I have a live broadcast at eleven.
You can't go on the air when your injury

53:17.319 --> 53:22.782
looks worse than your product. I worked
very hard to prepare my item.

53:29.039 --> 53:29.956
It's this way.

53:46.056 --> 53:49.643
I have a live broadcast at eleven.
You can't go on the air when your injury

53:49.726 --> 53:51.353
looks worse than your product.

54:05.408 --> 54:09.287
As you can see here, you can adjust the
intensity, so everyone from beginners

54:09.371 --> 54:12.791
to experts can exercise based on
their strength. Adjust it. Now grab

54:12.874 --> 54:16.378
the handle, and pull. And that's it.
You can do both cardio and weight

54:16.461 --> 54:19.965
training at the same time. Push
it with your lower body strength. Pull

54:20.048 --> 54:23.385
the handle toward your body, between
your belly button and core. That

54:23.468 --> 54:28.306
feels so good. Pull, forward and back.

54:32.102 --> 54:34.312
-It must hurt…
-Wow, it really feels like I'm actually

54:34.396 --> 54:36.398
rowing on water.

54:37.232 --> 54:40.610
That's amazing, I can actually feel it
already toning my arm.

54:44.906 --> 54:48.285
That's why I want it even more.
An essence derived from raw materials.

54:48.368 --> 54:50.078
I would love to show my customers.

54:58.003 --> 54:59.254
PROPOSAL FOR PARTNERSHIP

54:59.754 --> 55:01.172
HOME SHOPPING
DAM YE-JIN

55:14.519 --> 55:17.188
Jin-yi. Why are you here?

55:19.649 --> 55:23.028
You're a truly crappy landlord.
Not demanding rent from your tenant

55:23.111 --> 55:24.863
that's behind on payment?

55:26.364 --> 55:27.282
You don't have to pay.

55:27.365 --> 55:29.784
I've told you about a hundred different
times,

55:30.285 --> 55:32.037
don't treat me like a charity case.

55:35.957 --> 55:36.791
And Som-yi?

55:36.875 --> 55:39.502
Showing off the gift donated by
an anonymous person.

55:42.380 --> 55:44.049
Why was that woman here Hae-Seok?

55:50.513 --> 55:51.348
It's nothing.

55:53.350 --> 55:54.309
It's nothing?

55:59.105 --> 55:59.939
Hey!

56:03.193 --> 56:04.027
What do you want?

56:04.110 --> 56:07.405
The essence that Ms.Song's been preparing
for three years to release…

56:07.489 --> 56:08.573
It's about to drop.

56:09.282 --> 56:12.035
If customers buy the L'Etoile product,
are they really going to purchase

56:12.118 --> 56:14.496
-another essence?
-A good product always sells.

56:15.330 --> 56:17.415
Just focus on improving product quality.

56:19.000 --> 56:22.128
Do you have to sabotage Ms. Song to make
yourself feel better?

56:26.674 --> 56:31.638
Ah, poor Ms. Song. How sad. Ugh. You're
seriously so heartless.

56:55.578 --> 56:58.748
Hyung, let's settle things with L'Etoile
once and for all.

57:01.000 --> 57:03.420
Send me the full list of other buyers
right now.

57:19.936 --> 57:21.938
DAUGHTER,
YOU MUST BE BUSY

57:34.826 --> 57:38.204
Oh, there you are. Did you have dinner?

57:40.290 --> 57:41.416
I'm not very hungry.

57:44.627 --> 57:46.463
Let me cook you something, you must
be starving.

57:46.546 --> 57:47.797
Ow. Please, just…

57:48.298 --> 57:49.757
What's wrong? Are you hurt?

57:51.885 --> 57:53.136
It's nothing.

57:54.012 --> 57:55.138
You have to eat.

57:55.889 --> 57:59.392
Can you please stop bothering me
about some dinner? I'm too busy to be

57:59.476 --> 58:02.937
having dinner. How many times do I
have to tell you? It just makes me

58:03.021 --> 58:07.358
feel guilty when you keep making me food
that I don't eat.

58:11.321 --> 58:14.741
I'm just worried, it's fine if
you throw it out. I want to make sure

58:14.824 --> 58:17.785
you've got food in the fridge. In
case you are ever hungry.

58:19.329 --> 58:20.163
I mean…

58:22.457 --> 58:26.294
You need to stop coming over unannounced.
I'm not a kid? How many times must

58:26.377 --> 58:30.089
I say this? I'm a grown woman.

58:34.052 --> 58:38.932
Why do you always… just do whatever you
want?

58:45.104 --> 58:49.400
Ye-jin. Don't do it, Ye-jin. Don't do it.

58:50.109 --> 58:53.655
But it's true. Mom just abandoned me
and left.

58:54.822 --> 58:55.657
Ye-jin.

58:55.740 --> 58:58.701
I don't need this anymore. I'm gonna
reveal that Song Myeong-hwa's my mom and

58:58.785 --> 59:03.623
everything that comes from her mouth is
a lie.

59:04.916 --> 59:07.126
I'm the one who told her not to
contact you!

59:10.922 --> 59:11.756
What?

59:13.508 --> 59:17.387
The truth is… your mom had called me.
She said she acted that way because she

59:17.470 --> 59:24.352
was too scared, and she wanted
to apologize to you. But… I'm…

59:26.396 --> 59:29.607
I just couldn't bear to see you…
in so much pain again, my love.

59:30.358 --> 59:34.946
So I told her to never contact you again.
I am the one who told her that.

59:35.029 --> 59:37.782
Why… Why did you do that? What about me?
Why would you believe it's okay

59:37.865 --> 59:41.327
to do that by yourself? Why?

59:48.668 --> 59:49.502
I'm sorry.

59:54.382 --> 59:55.216
I'm so sorry.

01:00:11.316 --> 01:00:12.150
I'm sorry.

01:00:15.236 --> 01:00:16.112
I'm so sorry.

01:01:33.272 --> 01:01:34.107
Yes, hello.

01:01:35.024 --> 01:01:35.858
Mom.

01:01:38.611 --> 01:01:40.822
Listen, I told you before, miss.

01:01:40.905 --> 01:01:42.073
It's me, Ye-jin.

01:01:45.243 --> 01:01:46.077
What?

01:01:47.995 --> 01:01:49.580
Who did you say you were?

01:01:49.664 --> 01:01:56.421
Did you see the broadcast? Actually, I
was injured today.

01:02:09.016 --> 01:02:15.940
It hurt so much, every time I move…
I just wanted to give up…

01:02:19.360 --> 01:02:21.362
but it was a live show…

01:02:23.906 --> 01:02:25.116
So I powered through it.

01:02:29.704 --> 01:02:33.374
I did well, right, Mom? I'm pretty
professional, right?

01:02:33.875 --> 01:02:36.502
Ms. Dam Ye-jin, are you drunk perhaps?

01:02:36.586 --> 01:02:37.670
But…

01:02:39.839 --> 01:02:41.090
I guess today…

01:02:45.052 --> 01:02:46.304
I was pretty exhausted.

01:02:47.889 --> 01:02:50.224
I took it out on Dad for no reason.

01:02:51.058 --> 01:02:52.685
You might want to hang up and quit
talking.

01:02:52.769 --> 01:02:53.603
I'm such a mess.

01:02:54.645 --> 01:02:56.731
-Right?
-Hanging up now.

01:02:59.984 --> 01:03:02.820
Hello? Ms-- Ms. Dam Ye-jin!

01:03:13.122 --> 01:03:15.333
The number you have dialed is not
available…

01:03:27.386 --> 01:03:28.221
Mom.

01:03:31.349 --> 01:03:34.310
I miss you so much. Mom.

01:03:54.330 --> 01:03:55.414
I'm bleeding.

01:05:48.653 --> 01:05:50.446
SOLD OUT ON YOU

01:05:50.529 --> 01:05:53.574
THANK YOU MR. AHN SANG-WOO
FOR HIS SPECIAL APPEARANCE

01:06:20.810 --> 01:06:25.690
Aren't you curious if she slept well, or
missed a meal?

01:06:26.440 --> 01:06:28.109
Things are going well with Gojeuneok,
right?

01:06:28.192 --> 01:06:29.819
It's been a while, Mr. Lee.

01:06:30.319 --> 01:06:32.863
Nothing's gonna change no matter
what you do, Ms. Dam Ye-jin.

01:06:32.947 --> 01:06:35.032
They said they weren't going to buy
the corn?

01:06:35.116 --> 01:06:38.077
So, all this corn has turned into a real
headache.

01:06:38.160 --> 01:06:39.912
This isn't your business, Ms. Dam Ye-jin.

01:06:39.996 --> 01:06:41.163
-I have an idea.
-What?

01:06:44.375 --> 01:06:46.711
Ye-jin, your home shopping host.

01:06:46.794 --> 01:06:47.712
Ms. Dam Ye-jin,

01:06:48.295 --> 01:06:49.255
stay right there.
